TY  - JOUR
T1  - Anthropology and Economics
AU  - Posner, Richard A.
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260890
DO  - 10.1086/260890
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 608
EP  - 616
VL  - 88
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - The advance of economics into the traditional domains of other social sciences has thus far largely overlooked anthropology. In this review article on Frederic Pryor's The Origins of the Economy I argue that economics has many fruitful applications to the study of primitive society. I fault Pryor's book for its lack of a theoretical framework and argue that such a framework can be derived from the economics of information and uncertainty. In particular, it can be argued that many primitive social institutions are substitutes for formal markets in insurance.
AB  - The advance of economics into the traditional domains of other social sciences has thus far largely overlooked anthropology. In this review article on Frederic Pryor's The Origins of the Economy I argue that economics has many fruitful applications to the study of primitive society. I fault Pryor's book for its lack of a theoretical framework and argue that such a framework can be derived from the economics of information and uncertainty. In particular, it can be argued that many primitive social institutions are substitutes for formal markets in insurance.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260890
